minios-kernel-manager (1.1.0) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Fix CLI JSON output to report real running kernel state in `list` and
    `info` commands.
  * Add repository dependency resolution for split kernel packages using
    `apt-cache depends` and automatically include `linux-modules*` packages.
  * Add manual packaging support for multiple .deb files and return a clear
    error when a single selected package does not contain kernel modules.
  * Update GUI manual package picker to support selecting multiple .deb files.
  * Consolidate bootloader update flow by using bootloader_utils from
    minios_utils and preserve SYSLINUX lang/encoding handling.
  * Extend tests for dependency resolution and multi-package manual mode.

 -- crims0n <crims0n@minios.dev>  Sat, 28 Feb 2026 23:55:00 +0300

minios-kernel-manager (1.0.12) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Fix Python 3.6 SyntaxError in build_utils by removing duplicate
    subprocess.Popen keyword argument (universal_newlines).
    This restores `minios-kernel status --json` on bionic and fixes
    false read-only detection in the GUI.

 -- crims0n <crims0n@minios.dev>  Sat, 28 Feb 2026 22:14:30 +0300

minios-kernel-manager (1.0.11) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Code quality improvements:
    - Replace broad exception handlers with specific exception types
    - Improve error handling across all utility modules
  * Python 3.6 compatibility:
    - Lower Python requirement from 3.7 to 3.6 for Debian 10 support
    - Replace sys.stdout.reconfigure() with io.TextIOWrapper() wrapper
    - Replace capture_output=True with explicit stdout/stderr pipes
    - Replace text=True with universal_newlines=True in subprocess calls
    - Update debian/compat from 12 to 11
  * Testing infrastructure:
    - Add comprehensive pytest test suite
    - Add tests for minios_utils module (directory detection, kernel packaging,
      size formatting)
    - Add tests for kernel_utils module (kernel listing, apt repository parsing,
      package cache checking)
    - Add pytest.ini configuration file
    - Add conftest.py with common fixtures

 -- crims0n <crims0n@minios.dev>  Mon, 19 Jan 2026 17:40:49 +0300

